'CHOOSY LISTER' ALLOWS YOU TO SELECTANDTHEN LIST ANY RANGE OF BASICPROGRAM LINES FROM WITHIN A RUNNINGAPPLESOFT PROGRAM. TO USE IT;INSTALL THE ROUTINEAS THE FIRST TWOLINES IN YOUR PROGRAM;LINES 0 AND 1; AND MAKE SURE THATTHERE IS A LINE 10 IN YOUR PROGRAM.AT ANY POINT IN THE PROGRAM WHEREYOU WOULD LIKE TO LIST A USER-SELECTED RANGE OF LINES; INSERT A'GOSUB 1' INSTRUCTION.WHEN THE PROMPT 'L1;L2?' APPEARSDURING EXECUTION; ENTER THE FIRSTAND LAST LINENUMBERS IN THE RANGE.IT'S NOT NECESSARY TO INDICATE THEEXACT LINE NUMBERS: CHOOSY LISTERWILL LIST ANYLINES WITHIN THE SPECIFIED RANGE.THE ROUTINE CHANGES LINE 0 FROM AGOTO STATEMENT TO A 'LIST' COMMAND;LISTS THECHOSEN LINES; AND THENRESTORES LINE 0 TO ITS ORIGINALFORM.